 "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "biocmd.bio_task", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "biocmd.bio_task.create_task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflowcode", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "step", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "uniqueNo", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "biocmd.bio_task.list_task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflowcode", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "biocmd.entry", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "biocmd.entry.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["A simple biolab command client, See https://github.com/BioHubX/biocmd  for more detail information"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.workflow", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Define the dependencies between processes\n\nFor example: biocmd workflow create --name 'Strain Analysis pipeline' --code StrainAnalysis --step assembly --prestep qcstat --prestep datafilter\n\nThe above example means that creating a new pipeline requires specifying the name of the pipeline, the unique code of the pipeline, the name of the current algorithm of the pipeline, and the name of the pre-algorithm [\"qcstat\",\"datafilter\"] that the algorithm depends on"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.script", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Configure the algorithm used in the analysis flow\n\nFor example: biocmd script create --workflow StrainAnalysis --step qcstat --script biohubx/qcstat:v0.1.0\n\nThe above example means that creating an analysis algorithm requires specifying the name of a workflow, the name of the algorithm, and the algorithm implementation of the docker image corresponding to the algorithm"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.env", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Configure the Input,Output and Environment parameters of the algorithm\n\nFor example: biocmd env create --workflow StrainAnalysis --step qcstat --type Input --key file1 --feature _R1.fq.gz\n\nFor the above examples, that means that for the qcstat analysis algorithm in the StrainAnalysis workflow,a dependency on an input parameter is required, with the parameter name being file1, and the feature of the value of this parameter being that it contains _R1.fq.gz."]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Data file management,such as data registration\n\nFor example: biocmd file create --basedir /workspace/20241205\n\nThe above example means that the \"/workspace/20241205\" folder is used as the starting point to scan the address of the original sequencing file, which should meet certain format requirements, such as: /{baseDir}/{sampleNo}/{uniqueNo}/{sampleNo.R1.fq.gz},the final file structure looks like this:\n    sample1 => /workspace/20241205/sample1/unique1/sample1_R1.fq.gz\n    sample1 => /workspace/20241205/sample1/unique1/sample1_R2.fq.gz\n\n    sample2 => /workspace/20241205/sample2/unique2/sample2_R1.fq.gz\n    sample2 => /workspace/20241205/sample2/unique2/sample2_R2.fq.gz\n\n    and more ...\n\nsampleNo can same as uniqueNo"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Task management, such as starting a task and viewing a task\n\nFor example: biocmd task create --workflow StrainAnalysis --step qcstat --uniqueno sample1\n\nThe above example means that an StrainAnalysis_qcstat analysis task has been created for the sample1 (unique sample number)"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.server", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Configure the remote server environment, only support: server,parallel,outputDir\n\nFor example: biocmd server --key parallel --value 30\n\nThe biolab server specifies that the maximum concurrency capacity of the remote docker machine is 30 when doing automated scheduling (compute nodes can only allow a maximum of 30 tasks to be performed simultaneously)."]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.local", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Configure the remote server address, port, and token\n\nFor example: biocmd local set --server http://localhost --port 8080 --token xxxxxxxx\n\nThe above example means that the client is connected to the biolab server deployed at localhost, the service exposed port is 8080, and the token is a string automatically generated when the biolab service is started"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.set", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "server", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "port", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--server,--port, --port optional be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "code", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "step", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "prestep", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--name, --code, --step, --prestep must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflow", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--workflow must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflow", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "step", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "script", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--workflow, --step, --script must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflow", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--workflow must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflow", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "step", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "type", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "feature", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--workflow,--step, --type, --key, --feature must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflow", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "step", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--workflow,--step must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "basedir", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--basedir must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "uniqueno", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--uniqueno optional be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workflow", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "step", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "uniqueno", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--workflow,--step, --uniqueno must be provided"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["--key,--value must be provided", "@task.command()", "@click.option('--workflow', required=True, help='Unique pipeline code')", "def list(workflow):", "\"\"\"", "--workflow  must be provided", "\"\"\"", "bio_task.list_task(workflow)"]}, {"name": "biocmd.entry.list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["list all of the server config"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}